commitResults.messageTitle: chatbot can greet the user and exit
chatbot can echo user's input and exit when "bye" is entered.
chatbox now can store user's input and display back when requested.
user can mark tasks as done or not done. Task class is craeted to keep track of the task status.
Chatbot now can handle three types of tasks including ToDo, Deadline and Event.
Semi-automated UI testing and corrects some typo
Created several exception classes to handle invalid input.
User can delete tasks in the list.
Save and load data in and from the hard disk
commitResults.messageBody: When the chatbot starts, it loads data from the hard disk. A folder named data and a file named harper.txt are created if not exist. When the task list changes, data are restored into the file. When the content of the file does not follow the expected format, the chatbot will terminate.

Enhance date and time handling for task
commitResults.messageBody: Introduce the use of java.time.LocalDateTime to store date and time for Deadline and Event task. Display the date and time in a more user-friendly way: d MMM yyyy HH:mm (e.g., 20 Oct 2024 12:12).

commitResults.messageBody: Ui is creadted to deadl with interactions with user. Storage is created to dead with interactions with the file. TaskList is created to contain the tasks. Parser is created to make sense the command.

commitResults.messageTitle: Merge branch 'A-MoreOOP'
Reorganise different classes into corresponding packages
commitResults.messageBody: Package harper is the root package. Inside that, package commands contains all classes that handle different commands. Package exceptions contains all the exception classes. Package tasks contains three types of task. Package utils contains classes that handle different jobs.
